                                                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="mailto:?subject=Lakers%20offer%20Krzyzewski%20%2440%20million%20over%20five%20years%20|%20The%20Chronicle&amp;message=Check%20out%20this%20article%20from%20The%20Chronicle%3A%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dukechronicle.com%2Farticle%2F2004%2F07%2Flakers-offer-krzyzewski-40-million-over-five-years" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="email" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fa fa-envelope"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="#" onclick="window.print()" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fas fa-print"></i></a></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                
                <div class="article-content w-100 mb-4">
                                            <p>Men&rsquo;s basketball coach Mike Krzyzewski has been offered $8 million a year to coach the Los Angeles Lakers in a five-year contract, said multiple sources close to the situation.</p>
<p>Krzyzewski will likely announce whether he will accept the offer early next week, but few expect a decision before Monday.</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
            <div id="azk18664"></div>
    <!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
                        </div>

                        <p>Sources, speaking on the condition of anonymity, confirmed that the defection of Luol Deng and Shaun Livingston to the professional ranks upset Krzyzewski a great deal. As such, Krzyzewski&mdash;who one source said maintains complete and meticulous control over his program&mdash;was frustrated with NCAA regulations that limited his ability to compete with agents and professional teams for Deng and Livingston&rsquo;s attention.</p>
<p>Tom Butters, the former Duke Athletic Director that hired Krzyzewski from Army in 1980, believes the coach will have a great deal to consider over the course of the weekend.</p>
<p>&ldquo;He&rsquo;s going to have to measure what the opportunities are in front of him in L.A. against what a quarter of a century have provided him here,&rdquo; Butters told The Chronicle. &ldquo;If he were to leave and go to the Lakers and win 20 championships, he will always be associated with Duke basketball.&rdquo;</p>
<p>Krzyzewski&rsquo;s ability to adapt to the NBA is debated. Critics say the NBA game runs differently from college ball and coaches cannot adjust to the professional atmosphere. Rick Pitino and Jerry Tarkanian, among others, tried to make the jump but met with limited success. Both returned to college basketball.</p>
<p>People who have worked with Krzyzewski, however, say his coaching skills are fungible.</p>
<p>&ldquo;His strength is relationships,&rdquo; said Tom Mickle, who worked in the Duke athletic department for the first eight years of Krzyzewski&rsquo;s reign. &ldquo;He can build a team, team chemistry, as well as anybody. I don&rsquo;t think he&rsquo;d have any trouble succeeding at any level.&rdquo;</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
        <div id="azk5125"></div>
<!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
                        </div>

                                                                            <p>Sources said Kobe Bryant, the Lakers&rsquo; star guard, specifically asked owner Jerry Buss to hire Krzyzewski.</p>
<p>Krzyzewski has remained elusive, however, as he has not been available to the media since a Tuesday press conference when he derided the NBA for hampering the college &ldquo;brand&rdquo;. Although Krzyzewski was in talks with the Lakers and University officials at that time, no knowledge of these discussions broke until Thursday afternoon.</p>
<p>Since then, Krzyzewski has not spoken to the media. Even his older brother, William, has been unable to speak with the Hall of Fame coach.</p>
<p>&ldquo;I know he&rsquo;s been tough to get ahold of,&rdquo; the older Krzyzewski told The Chronicle from his home in Chicago. &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve been trying.&rdquo;</p>
                            

<div class="mc-signup my-4 p-4 text-center " id="mc-container" data-mc="58dfdea1a4">
    <h3>Get Overtime, all Duke athletics</h3>
    <p>Signup for our editorially curated, weekly newsletter. Cancel at any time.</p>
